  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "This package documents a credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The underlying computational model has been applied in clinical research settings to support ventricular assist device (VAD) design decisions, and practitioners have used its outputs to inform Class III device submissions. Model Risk Level 5 drives stricter credibility requirements across all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. Despite these gaps, the assessment team accepted the model for the current decision context based on conservative bounding arguments and sensitivity analyses. No structured Context of Use record is attached to this unit; intended-use scope is described only in this narrative.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-piv-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-bench-measurements-2023"
  ],
